text:
17th IBBF - tap
amber/brown colour, clear, small foam, grassy and a little herbal aroma, some caramel notes; medium body, medium bitterness, lightly sweet; rather lightly bodied, somewhat metallic feel, average carbonation, long bitter and dry finish;
Overall: quite refreshing and drinkable, nice taste and palate

Aroma: hops, malt;
Appearance: nice bottle, nice red-copper color, good head;
Flavor: some sweet, bitter, malt;
Palate: very nice, lingers;
Overall: good taste, worth trying again;
Bought at Trinkgut, Kleve, Germany.
On tap at the brewery (very nice)
